import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='precipitation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across the locations?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='temp_range', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('How does the temperature range vary across the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature Range')
    plt.legend(title='Temperature Range', loc='upper right')

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='wind', y='precipitation', hue='location')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between wind and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Location')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax, color='blue', width=0.4, position=0)
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='temp_min', data=data, ax=ax, color='red', width=0.4, position=1)

    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of temperature max and temperature min across the locations?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(['Temp Max', 'Temp Min'])

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year

    weather_counts = data.groupby(['year', 'weather']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    weather_counts_pivot = weather_counts.pivot_table(index='year', columns='weather', values='count', fill_value=0)

    ax = weather_counts_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title("What is the most common weather condition across the years?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(title="Weather", loc="upper left")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
